Reunification through Great National Unity Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 18 (KCNA) --To achieve the great unity of the whole nation stands out as a serious and urgent matter concerning its destiny today when the country remains divided, declares Rodong Sinmun Thursday in its signed article.
 Noting that national reunification is a cause of reconnecting the blood veins of the nation divided into north and south and achieving national unity, the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reunification of the country is unthinkable apart from great national unity, which is, so to speak, the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle for the great unity of the nation has entered a new higher stage in the June 15 era of reunification which is the first to be unfolded in the history of division. "By our nation itself," the main idea of the historic June 15 joint declaration, is the idea of national sovereignty and, at the same time, the idea of great national unity. It expounds the idea of achieving independent reunification through reconciliation and close unity of the Korean nation, the master of national reunification, rejecting foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the banner of "By our nation itself", the Korean nation is confidently carrying on the struggle for great unity without vacillation and frustration in face of internal and external challenges and ordeals of every description. All these are a brilliant fruition of the great idea of the great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the wise leadership of leader Kim Jong Il, the historic Pyongyang meeting, the first of its kind in the history of national division, was realized and the June 15 joint declaration adopted. This opened a new era of independent national reunification in which the reconciliation and unity of the nation are becoming a living reality at a new higher stage under the banner of "By our nation itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fellow countrymen of Korea are overflowing with the conviction and optimism that independent reunification is sure to be achieved by the great unity of the whole nation, for they have the great idea and line of the great national unity and hold in high esteem the brilliant commander of the Songun revolution at the head of the nation.

GNP's Desperate Moves to Keep NSL in Force under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 18 (KCNA) -- The ultra-right conservative forces including the Grand National Party of south Korea have turned the National Assembly into a platform of scramble between the ruling and opposition parties and a centre for fanning up confrontation with the north. The anti-reform moves of the ultra-right conservatives have placed the elementary democracy won by the south Koreans at the cost of blood in the danger of being trampled down upon. Rodong Sinmun Thursday says this in a signed commentary.
 This is clearly evidenced by the fact that the issue of abolishing the "National Security Law," a unanimous demand of the south Koreans from all walks of life, has failed to find a solution due to their desperate moves, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their desperate opposition to the repeal of the NSL is an intolerable mockery of the destiny and future of the south Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the south Koreans except a few ultra-right conservatives within the GNP who support the U.S. in its acts against national reunification are falling victim to the draconic NSL. This clearly proves that the NSL is a leftover of the old times which should have already been eradicated and that if this law is allowed to remain in force the north-south confrontation will further deteriorate to spark nothing but a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes without saying that neither dialogue nor national cooperation nor the independent reunification of the country is possible with the NSL remaining in force as it designates the north as an "anti-state organization" and the northerners an "enemy". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean ultra-right conservatives' desperate efforts to keep the NSL in force are aimed to justify their fascist suppression and their moves to escalate the confrontation with the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The patriotic-minded people in south Korea should go united to completely deter the GNP from desperately working to bring back the old era of confrontation.

Art Show of Mansudae Art Studio Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 18 (KCNA) -- An art show of the Mansudae Art Studio opened at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition on Nov. 17.
 On display are art works showing the undying revolutionary feats of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and their noble traits and more than 400 pieces of excellent art works including Korean paintings, oils, graphic paintings, sculptures, Korean jewel paintings, and crafts and embroideries. Among them are the Korean paintings "Tracing Memories" and "Light of the Paradise," the oil "The Dawn of Mupho" and the acrylic painting "Defending the Safety of the General" which depict the immortal revolutionary exploits of the peerlessly great men brilliantly recorded in the annuals of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also exhibited at the show are the acrylic painting "The First Footprints of Songun Leadership", the Korean painting "With Paternal Affection", the oil "Greeting Tree Planting Day among Soldiers" and other paintings successfully depicting the great traits of leader Kim Jong Il who makes the endless long journey of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also drawing the attention of the visitors are Korean paintings showing the eight beauty spots of Songun including "Sunrise on Mt. Paektu", the oil "Young Scientists", the sculpture "Enrollment in the Army" and other works representing the purpose and emotion of the people in the Songun era.

Korean Food Served in Pyongyang Restaurants 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 18 (KCNA) -- Restaurant serving Korean food has appeared in each district of Pyongyang, the capital of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Kim Ki Myong, a section chief of the Public Catering Management Department of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, told KCNA that the department, after consultation with officials concerned, standardized the cooking methods of traditional dishes inherent in the Pyongyang area and chose kinds of folk dishes for each restaurant according to its actual condition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pothonggang Restaurant on the picturesque bank of the River Pothong serves boiled rice and soup, rice-cake, noodle and pancake, Tangogi soup, green gram pancake and mullet soup famous in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is crowded with many people including old men and women and children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Some people come to the restaurant with their families and enjoy the Korean food. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The section chief added that his department will direct efforts to developing more traditional dishes inherent in Pyongyang.

Songun Politics to Be Continued in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 18 (KCNA) -- It is the unshakable will of leader Kim Jong Il to defend and accomplish the Korean revolution, started with arms, relying on the armed forces.
 True to the behests of President Kim Il Sung, he carried forward the leadership based on Songun politics with an inspection of an army unit ten years ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the Korean people were overwhelmed by grief after the President passed away, Kim Jong Il issued an order of the supreme commander of the Korean People's Army on building Chongryu Bridge (second stage) and Kumnung Tunnel No. 2, the first order to implement the President's behests. When inspecting the construction site of the Nyongwon Power Station, he told officials that the behests of the President should be implemented without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has continued his Songun-based leadership, saying that he should go anywhere, if it is for the implementation of the President's behests, and that doing so is his unswerving will and invariable creed as he took over the chairmanship of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and the supreme commandership from the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through his uninterrupted inspection of army units he has strengthened the army to be a strong revolutionary army defending the leader at the cost of their lives and an invincible army no enemy can match. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Signal successes have been registered in science and the economy, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Typical of them are the launch of artificial satellite Kwangmyongsong No.1, completion of Juche-oriented iron-making methods, successful cloning, construction of the Anbyon Youth Power Station, Youth Hero Highway and Pyongyang-Hyangsan Tourist Motorway, modern chicken farms and fish farms and standardization of co-op fields.

Yang Hyong Sop Meets Chinese Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 18 (KCNA) -- Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly conversation with a delegation headed by Xing Yunming, vice-president of the China Association for International Friendly Contact, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Thursday.
 The head of the delegation said the Chinese people deeply revere President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il. While staying in Korea, we were deeply impressed to see the successes achieved by the Korean people in socialist construction, he noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The friendly ties between the two countries provided by Kim Il Sung and revolutionaries of the elder generation of China are daily growing stronger under the deep care of General Secretary Hu Jintao and General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Jon Yong Jin, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the Korea-China Friendship Association who is also vice-chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and Guan Huabing, charge d' affaires ad interim of the Chinese embassy here.
